# Example .ccrshadow file.
#
# Copy this to .ccrshadow in any project workspace to filter paths between
# the host and the container. ccr-fuse reads this at container start; see
# docs/adr/0003-strict-gitignore-subset-and-ccrshadow-filename.md for the
# rationale behind the filename and syntax.
#
# Syntax: strict subset of .gitignore (one pattern per line).
#   *           any sequence of chars except '/'
#   **          any number of path components (zero or more)
#   ?           a single char except '/'
#   [abc]       character class
#   /pattern    leading slash anchors the pattern to the workspace root
#   pattern/    trailing slash restricts the pattern to directories
#   pattern     unanchored (no slash anywhere except trailing) matches at any depth
#   a/b/c       any mid-pattern slash anchors to root (per .gitignore spec)
#
# Limitations:
#   * No negation (`!pattern`) — silently skipped with a warning.
#   * Lines starting with `#` are comments; inline `#` is literal.
#   * Path traversal patterns (`..`) are rejected.
#   * Only the workspace-root `.ccrshadow` is read; nested files are ignored.
#
# Semantics for every matched path:
#   * Host's matching file/dir is INVISIBLE inside the container.
#     stat returns ENOENT until the container writes something there.
#   * Container creates/writes/deletes go to a container-local "shadow store"
#     (/var/lib/ccr/shadow) — they NEVER touch the host filesystem.
#   * The shadow store survives `ccr stop`/`start`. `ccr destroy` wipes it;
#     host content is unaffected either way.
#
# Risks worth knowing (see docs/adr/0004-cross-region-rename-keeps-exdev.md):
#   * `mv shadowed/file passthrough-name` copies container-generated content
#     to host disk. Use `cp + rm` deliberately if you mean it.
#
# Two typical use cases:
#   1. Secrets the container should not see (.env*, credentials, ssh keys).
#   2. Build artifacts whose architecture differs from the host (node_modules,
#      .venv, target, etc.) — the container builds its own copy.

# Secrets / private files (unanchored: at any depth)
.env.local
.env.production
.env.*.local
.aws/credentials
.ssh/id_rsa
.ssh/id_ed25519

# Build artifacts that should live only in the container
node_modules
.venv
target
.next
dist
__pycache__
*.pyc

# Local logs (any depth)
*.log

# A root-anchored example: hides /secret at root but NOT a/secret
# /secret

# A dir-anchored example: build/ at any depth, only directories
# build/
